Find and fix the bug in this code:

```typescript
const sfxId = cc.audioEngine.playEffect('res/audio/sfx_loop.mp3', true);

// Later, try to stop it
cc.audioEngine.stopEffect(sfxId);
// Error: sometimes sfxId is null!
```

output:
The bug is that `playEffect` returns `number | null`, and passing `null` to `stopEffect` causes an error. The effect might fail to play if the file isn't loaded or the engine has too many concurrent sounds.

**Fixed code:**
```typescript
// Preload first to ensure reliability
cc.audioEngine.preloadEffect('res/audio/sfx_loop.mp3');

const sfxId = cc.audioEngine.playEffect('res/audio/sfx_loop.mp3', true);

// Always null-check before using the ID
if (sfxId !== null) {
    // Later, stop it safely
    cc.audioEngine.stopEffect(sfxId);
}
```

Two fixes: (1) preload the effect to reduce the chance of `null` return, and (2) always null-check the return value of `playEffect` before storing or using the audio ID. Store the ID only when non-null to avoid errors in later `stopEffect`/`pauseEffect` calls.

